about.summary: A simple to use summary function that can be used with pipes and displays nicely in the console. The default summary statistics may be modified by the user as can the default formatting. Support for data frames and vectors is included, and users can implement their own skim methods for specific object types as described in a vignette. Default summaries include support for inline spark graphs. Instructions for managing these on specific operating systems are given in the "Using skimr" vignette and the README.

name: r-skimr
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "2.1.3" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-skimr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/skimr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/skimr/skimr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 41510c514ce65c86642b0165e3fb03b0fad17e58eb95f29a00a6261568a0050b

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-crayon
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0
    - r-knitr >=1.2
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrr
    - r-repr
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-stringr >=1.1
    - r-tibble >=2.0.0
    - r-tidyr >=1.0
    - r-tidyselect >=0.2.5
    - r-vctrs
    - r-withr
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-cli
    - r-crayon
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.0
    - r-knitr >=1.2
    - r-magrittr >=1.5
    - r-purrr
    - r-repr
    - r-rlang >=0.3.1
    - r-stringr >=1.1
    - r-tibble >=2.0.0
    - r-tidyr >=1.0
    - r-tidyselect >=0.2.5
    - r-vctrs
    - r-withr

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('skimr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('skimr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://docs.ropensci.org/skimr (website), https://github.com/ropensci/skimr
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: A simple to use summary function that can be used with pipes and displays nicely in the console. The default summary statistics may be modified by the user as can the default formatting. Support for data frames and vectors is included, and users can implement their own skim methods for specific object types as
    described in a vignette. Default summaries include support for inline spark graphs. Instructions for managing these on specific operating systems are given in the "Using skimr" vignette and the README.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
